cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with logic programming and its complexity.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of logic programs and rewriting rules.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper introduces an algebraic counterpart of the memoization technique.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper characterizes deterministic polynomial time computation.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper uses an encoding of pushdown automata.
